# Cursor Rules for Budget Genie

# This file helps Cursor follow the same patterns as the project

## Project Context

- Framework: React 18 + TypeScript with Vite 7.3.1
- State: Zustand (use-media-plan-store is the central store)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + Shadcn/UI components
- Testing: Vitest (102+ tests)
- Build: npm run build, dev: npm run dev

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript for all new code (.ts, .tsx)
- Component files: PascalCase (e.g., OutputNav.tsx)
- Hooks: use-kebab-case (e.g., use-media-plan-store.ts)
- Utility functions: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## Component Patterns

- Use functional components with hooks exclusively
- Prefer composition over prop drilling - use React Context when state is shared
- Use useMemo/useCallback to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Always declare memoized values explicitly with useMemo

## State Management

- All plan data flows through useMediaPlanStore (Zustand)
- Derived metrics computed via useChannelsWithMetrics() selector
- Use persist middleware for localStorage auto-save
- Actions should be pure functions in the store

## Testing

- Write unit tests for logic files (lib/ and types/)
- Use vitest for all tests (run with: npm run test:run)
- Mock Zustand store in component tests via vi.mock()
- Test file pattern: filename.test.ts

## File Organization

src/
├── pages/ # Full-page components (route views)
├── components/ # Reusable UI components
│ ├── dashboard/ # Dashboard-specific components
│ ├── onboarding/ # Wizard and setup flows
│ ├── import/ # Import/upload components
│ ├── common/ # Shared UI patterns
│ └── ui/ # Shadcn/UI primitives
├── hooks/ # Custom React hooks (Zustand selectors)
├── contexts/ # React Context providers
├── lib/ # Pure utility functions and business logic
├── types/ # TypeScript interfaces and enums
└── store/ # Zustand store instances (not hooked)

## Key Files to Understand

- src/hooks/use-media-plan-store.ts — Central Zustand store (all plan data)
- src/types/channel.ts — Channel math engine (calculateUnifiedMetrics)
- src/lib/vertical-presets.ts — Preset configurations for each vertical
- src/components/onboarding/OnboardWizard.tsx — New user setup flow
- src/pages/Output.tsx — Client-facing plan report

## Common Tasks

1. Add a new channel metric → Edit calculateUnifiedMetrics() in src/types/channel.ts
2. Add a new UI setting → Add to GlobalMultipliers in use-media-plan-store
3. New filtering logic → Create selector hook in use-media-plan-store
4. New page route → Create .tsx in src/pages/, lazy-import in App.tsx
5. New validation rule → Add test in src/lib/\*.test.ts, implement in lib/

## API Integration

- Supabase: src/lib/supabase.ts (auth, plan storage, realtime)
- Google Generative AI: used for narrative generation (VITE_GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY env var)
- stripe-webhook function: handles subscription status updates

## Performance Notes

- All channel calculations are memoized (useChannelsWithMetrics selector)
- Filters recursively remove inactive channels → O(n) but acceptable for ~30 channels max
- Animations: use Tailwind animate classes (avoid raw CSS for consistency)
- Images lazy-loaded where possible

## Common Gotchas

1. REV_SHARE channels need secondaryPrice (%) set to calculate metrics
2. FLAT_FEE/RETAINER spend is computed from allocation % during wizard (not preset price)
3. Horizontal scroll tables: wrap in overflow-x-auto + w-full
4. Modal dialogs: use Shadcn Dialog for consistency
5. Toast notifications: use sonner toast() (never raw window.alert)
